I've confirmed the bug. The SVG minifier strips the `x-on:click` attribute because `x-on` isn't in the known namespaces list.

Now I need to understand where the fix should go. The issue is in the `tdewolff/minify` library's SVG minifier. Looking at the SVG minifier code at `/go/pkg/mod/github.com/tdewolff/minify/v2@v2.24.10/svg/svg.go`, line 186-199:

```go
// skip attributes in namespace (eg. inkscape or sodipodi)
if colon := bytes.IndexByte(t.Text, ':'); colon != -1 {
    keep := false
    prefix, name := ToHash(t.Text[:colon]), ToHash(t.Text[colon+1:])
    for _, ns := range namespaces {
        if prefix == ns || tag == Svg && prefix == Xmlns && name == ns {
            keep = true
            break
        }
    }
    if !keep {
        continue
    }
}
```

This code strips any attribute that has a colon prefix that isn't in the `namespaces` list (which only contains `Xlink`). This is what drops AlpineJS attributes like `x-on:click`.

The fix should be in the `tdewolff/minify` library, not in Hugo. But since this is a Hugo bug fix task, perhaps the fix should be applied to the minify library via an update, or Hugo should override this behavior.

